# NOTE: firebase-config.js is intentionally NOT ignored in this repo.
# This connects to an isolated demo Firebase project with only fictional
# data — Firebase API keys aren't secret by design (protection comes from
# Firestore Security Rules, already published). Do NOT do this for a repo
# connected to a real production project with real user data — use
# firebase-config.example.js as the template instead, and keep the real
# firebase-config.js out of version control in that case.
